<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b>Step 2: Check Pump Tags and Build AF Import Data<=
o:p></o:p></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b>2.1) Check all pump tags<o:p></o:p></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.5in">check_all_pump_tags()&nbs=
p;generates 16 tag candidates per station (4 pumps x 4 measurements: RUN, F=
RQ, RSPD, CSPD) and validates each against the PI Web API.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.5in"><b><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></b><=
/p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.5in"><b>2.2) Identify multi-pu=
mp and VFD stations<o:p></o:p></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.5in">get_scada_history()&nbsp;=
pulls 7 days of SCADA history for valid tags (excluding P1RUN/P2RUN).<o:p><=
/o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.5in">check_multiple_pumps_or_v=
fd_control()&nbsp;analyzes the history to identify stations with more than =
2 pumps or VFD speed control. Stations with &gt;2 pumps are excluded from t=
he standard template flow.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.5in"><b><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></b><=
/p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.5in"><b>2.3) Check lead setpoi=
nt tags<o:p></o:p></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.5in">For remaining stations, c=
hecks if a&nbsp;_WLLEADSP&nbsp;tag exists. Stations with a lead setpoint ge=
t the&nbsp;_cte_leadsp&nbsp;template; those without get&nbsp;_cte_lead.<o:p=
></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.5in"><b><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></b><=
/p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.5in"><b>2.4) Join reference da=
ta and export<o:p></o:p></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.5in">Joins with plant basin as=
signments (get_ls_by_plant()) and wetwell diameter data (get_dia_by_ls()). =
These are currently loaded from RData files but are placeholder functions i=
ntended to be replaced with computed
 lookups.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.5in">Exports to&nbsp;data/pi_a=
f_import.csv&nbsp;with columns: BASIN, STATION_NAME, CMMS_ASSET_ID, PI_TAG,=
 Dia, TEMPLATE<o:p></o:p></p>
